{#- LLM-facing text is English-only: Cyrillic uses roughly 2–3× more tokens per word.
    This Jinja comment is stripped and never sent to the model.
    docs/MEMORY_TABLE.md §3 / docs/INDEX.md §7: tool-spec for route `reflect`. -#}
{
  "type": "function",
  "function": {
    "name": "reflect",
    "description": "Maze move — REMAP: rebuild the whole map, do not walk on blind. Not a substitute for memory_query/cli_intent. Request another reasoning cycle that re-runs the enrich graph retrieval (a fresh hybrid traversal of the unified knowledge/memory graph) with a new formulation. Use when a targeted memory_query cannot connect the entities you need and a broad, multi-entity refresh is warranted — not a different system, the same graph re-queried. Use only when re-enrich will add information. Do not copy prior turns — provide a short summary and an explicit clarification request that names the entities and the links you expect, so the graph query planner can rebuild a richer sample.\n\nWhen NOT to use: as a substitute for file/repo search — run memory_query and cli_intent (rg/find/cat) discovery first; reflect does not read the filesystem. If you have not yet tried at least one targeted memory_query for the missing entities, do that before reflect.",
    "parameters": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "reasoning": {
          "type": "string",
          "minLength": 1,
          "maxLength": 500,
          "description": "Brief explanation of why current context is insufficient and what you expect the reflect cycle to provide."
        },
        "summary": {
          "type": "string",
          "minLength": 1,
          "maxLength": 4000,
          "description": "Brief summary of current reasoning (known facts, conclusions in progress)."
        },
        "clarification_request": {
          "type": "string",
          "minLength": 1,
          "maxLength": 4000,
          "description": "What to clarify or expand next — question or hypothesis for the graph retrieval. List the entities and the hypothesized links you want the planner to explore. Target the root cause or the unresolved sub-question, not a restatement of what you already know."
        }
      },
      "required": ["reasoning", "summary", "clarification_request"],
      "additionalProperties": false
    }
  }
}
